# в”Ђв”Ђ Only needed for the `supabase` data layer в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# The default data layer is `local` (SQLite + a self-issued JWT), which needs
# NO account, NO keys, and NO .env at all вЂ” just clone and run. Fill this in
# only if you chose the `supabase` data layer during scoping.
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ

# Supabase project URL (Settings в†’ API)
SUPABASE_URL=

# Supabase publishable key (formerly "anon key"). Safe to expose client-side.
# Find it under Project Settings в†’ API Keys (the new tab, not Legacy).
SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Supabase secret key (formerly "service_role key"). Server-side only, never ship to the client.
# Find it under Project Settings в†’ API Keys. Click "Reveal" to see the value.
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=

# Supabase direct database URL вЂ” used by migrate.js to create tables automatically.
# Get it from: Supabase Dashboard в†’ Settings в†’ Database в†’ Connection string в†’ URI (Session mode, port 5432)
# It looks like: postgresql://postgres.[ref]:[password]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
# You create and copy the password when you set up the database when creating the Supabase project. 
DATABASE_URL=